fields.itinerary_description: Experience the best of Thailand in 5 days with a trip to Bangkok and Chiang Mai. Immerse yourself in the bustling city life of Bangkok, and then venture north to explore the cultural treasures of Chiang Mai.

fields.description: Explore the iconic landmarks such as Eiffel Tower, Louvre Museum, and Notre-Dame Cathedral.
Relax on the beautiful beaches of Nice and enjoy the vibrant atmosphere of the Promenade des Anglais.
Discover the prestigious vineyards of Bordeaux, enjoy wine tastings, and explore the UNESCO-listed city center.
Indulge in gastronomic delights in Lyon, known as the food capital of France, and visit the historic Old Town.
Experience the vibrant culture of Marseille, explore the picturesque Vieux Port, and stroll along the coastal promenade.
Experience the glitz and glamour of the famous Cannes Film Festival, stroll along the elegant Croisette Boulevard, and relax on the sandy beaches.
Discover the awe-inspiring medieval abbey perched on a rocky island, surrounded by vast tidal flats.
Immerse yourself in the enchanting blend of French and German influences, explore the charming Petite France neighborhood and visit the stunning Strasbourg Cathedral.
Experience the vibrant pink city, known for its aerospace industry, rich history, and distinctive red-brick architecture.
Visit the UNESCO World Heritage-listed historic center, including the impressive Palais des Papes and the famous Avignon Bridge.

Return to the Yasawa Islands to fully embrace the island paradise. Spend your days snorkeling, kayaking, or simply unwinding on the powdery beaches while enjoying the breathtaking views of the Pacific.

Denarau Island is a luxury resort area known for its beautiful beaches, golf courses, and upscale accommodations. Enjoy a day of relaxation on the pristine shores, indulge in water sports, or take a boat trip to the nearby Mamanuca Islands.

Vanua Levu is the second-largest island in Fiji and offers a more off-the-beaten-path experience. Explore the untouched rainforests, visit traditional Fijian villages, and enjoy the peaceful atmosphere of this tropical paradise.
End your trip by returning to Nadi. Spend your final day souvenir shopping, taking a relaxing spa treatment, or simply enjoying the serene beaches before departing from Fiji.

Beqa Island is known for its stunning coral reefs and thrilling shark diving experiences. Immerse yourself in the underwater world while diving with sharks or relax on the pristine sandy beaches of this secluded island.
Explore the stunning beaches of Copacabana and Ipanema, visit the iconic Christ the Redeemer statue, and enjoy the vibrant nightlife.
Experience the bustling metropolis of Sao Paulo, known for its vibrant culture, diverse cuisine, and impressive skyline.
Embark on a unique adventure in the heart of the Amazon rainforest, explore the diverse wildlife, and visit local indigenous communities.
Discover the vibrant city of Recife, known for its beautiful beaches, lively culture, and historic center.
Immerse yourself in the rich Afro-Brazilian culture of Salvador, visit historic colonial buildings, and enjoy traditional music and dance.
Step back in time and witness the well-preserved colonial architecture of Ouro Preto, a UNESCO World Heritage site.
Explore the awe-inspiring Iguazu Falls, a natural wonder shared by Brazil and Argentina, surrounded by lush rainforest.
Escape to the pristine beaches and crystal-clear waters of Fernando de Noronha, a paradise for diving and snorkeling enthusiasts.
Brazil's largest city, offering a bustling cosmopolitan experience with diverse cultural attractions and a vibrant nightlife.
Experience the charm of Paraty, a historical coastal town with cobblestone streets, colorful buildings, and nearby tropical islands.
Head to Florianópolis for beautiful beaches, great surf spots, and a relaxed island lifestyle.
Explore the modernist architecture of Brazil's capital city, including the famous government buildings and impressive urban planning.
Discover the natural wonders of Bonito, known for its crystal-clear rivers, impressive caves, and abundant wildlife.
Explore the vibrant city of Barcelona with its unique architecture, beautiful beaches, and bustling street markets.
Visit the capital city of Spain, Madrid, and experience its rich culture, world-class museums, and lively nightlife.
Discover the enchanting city of Seville, known for its stunning architecture, flamenco dancing, and delicious tapas.
Famous for the stunning Alhambra palace and the historic Albaicín neighborhood
An island known for its vibrant nightlife, crystal-clear waters, and beautiful beaches
Known for its futuristic City of Arts and Sciences and delicious paella
Visit the Valley of the Fallen, a monument and basilica located near Madrid, dedicated to those who died during the Spanish Civil War.
Indulge in the culinary delights of San Sebastian, renowned for its Michelin-starred restaurants, beautiful beaches, and charming old town.
Explore the ancient ruins of the Roman Empire and visit famous landmarks like the Colosseum and the Vatican City.
Marvel at Renaissance art in the Uffizi Gallery, visit the Duomo, and stroll across the Ponte Vecchio.
Take a romantic gondola ride along the canals and visit St. Mark's Square
Discover the fashion capital of Italy, see Leonardo da Vinci's 'The Last Supper', and visit the magnificent Milan Cathedral.
Hike along the picturesque coastal trail connecting the colorful villages of Monterosso, Vernazza, Corniglia, Manarola, and Riomaggiore.

A town located in the Pyrenees, perfect for outdoor enthusiasts and nature lovers.
A picturesque village surrounded by mountains, popular for outdoor activities like hiking and skiing.
A small town with beautiful architecture and a rich cultural heritage, offering opportunities for sightseeing and exploring Andorra's history.

Bucharest, the capital of Romania, is known for its stunning architecture, vibrant nightlife, and rich history. Explore the iconic Palace of the Parliament, take a leisurely stroll in the beautiful Herastrau Park, and visit the historic Village Museum.

Brașov is a charming city nestled in the Carpathian Mountains. Enjoy a scenic drive through the picturesque Transylvania region to reach this medieval town. Visit the famous Black Church, explore the old town with its colorful houses and narrow streets, and take a cable car ride to the top of Mount Tâmpa for panoramic views.
The unofficial capital of Transylvania, renowned for its cultural scene, lively atmosphere, and beautiful architecture.
A charming city nestled in the Carpathian Mountains, famous for its medieval architecture and proximity to Bran Castle, also known as Dracula's Castle.
Saranda is a popular coastal town in southern Albania. It offers beautiful beaches, crystal-clear waters, and is a gateway to the ancient ruins of Butrint National Park.
Tirana is the capital and largest city of Albania. It is known for its vibrant energy, with a mix of modern and communist-era architecture.
Gjirokaster is another UNESCO World Heritage Site in Albania. It is known for its Ottoman-style houses, cobblestone streets, and its imposing hilltop castle.
Berat is a historic city known as the 'City of a Thousand Windows'. It is famous for its well-preserved Ottoman-era houses and its medieval castle.
Explore the capital city of Northern Ireland, see the Titanic Belfast museum, visit the Giant's Causeway, and discover the vibrant street art scene in the Cathedral Quarter.
A charming coastal city with a bohemian atmosphere and a lively arts scene. Explore the colorful streets of Galway and enjoy traditional Irish music in its pubs.
Discover the ancient history of Limerick, visit the stunning King John's Castle, and explore the charming streets lined with Georgian architecture and medieval relics.
The capital city of Ireland, known for its vibrant nightlife and historical landmarks such as Dublin Castle and Trinity College.
Visit the second largest city in Ireland, known for its rich history, lively markets, and proximity to the beautiful countryside of County Cork.
A beautiful island known for its stunning sunsets, white-washed buildings, and blue-domed churches.
The capital city of Greece with historical landmarks such as the Acropolis and Parthenon.

Plovdiv is the second-largest city in Bulgaria and is famous for its well-preserved Roman architecture. Explore the Ancient Theatre of Plovdiv, the Roman Stadium, and the charming Old Town with its cobblestone streets and traditional houses.

Sofia is the capital and largest city of Bulgaria. It offers a blend of modern and historical attractions, including the Alexander Nevsky Cathedral and the Vitosha Mountain. Sofia is also known for its vibrant nightlife and delicious cuisine.

Burgas is located on the Bulgarian Black Sea coast and offers beautiful sandy beaches and a vibrant summer atmosphere. Enjoy the relaxing beach vibes, visit the Sea Garden, and explore the nearby town of Nessebar, which is a UNESCO World Heritage Site.

Veliko Tarnovo is a picturesque town with a rich history. Visit the Tsarevets Fortress, marvel at the stunning views from the Gurko Street, and wander around the Samovodska Charshiya Street, known for its craft shops and traditional Bulgarian products.
A lively university town with a rich cultural scene, known for its art museums and scenic coastline.
The capital city of Denmark, known for its beautiful architecture, historic sites, and vibrant restaurant scene.
A charming city filled with historic sites, including an impressive medieval castle and a vibrant waterfront.
Capital city of Germany with rich history and vibrant nightlife
Famous for its stunning cathedral and vibrant arts scene
Bavaria's cultural and beer capital famous for Oktoberfest
Sintra is a fairytale-like town located just outside of Lisbon. It is famous for its romantic, palatial architecture and enchanting landscapes. A visit to Sintra is like stepping into a storybook.
Porto is a charming city known for its port wine cellars, colorful buildings, and beautiful waterfront. It offers a perfect mix of history, culture, and delicious food.
Lisbon is the capital and largest city of Portugal. It is a vibrant and dynamic city with a rich history and stunning architecture.
Faro is a charming city in southern Portugal, famous for its beautiful beaches and vibrant Old Town. Explore the medieval walls of Faro Cathedral and relax on the sandy shores of Praia de Faro.
Vik is a picturesque village on Iceland's south coast. Marvel at the black sand beaches, visit the Reynisfjara basalt columns, and take a hike to the nearby Dyrhólaey peninsula.
Located in northern Iceland, Akureyri is a charming town with stunning landscapes. Enjoy the beauty of Godafoss waterfall, explore the botanical gardens, and take a whale-watching tour.

The capital city of Iceland is known for its vibrant arts scene, colorful houses, and lively nightlife. Visit the iconic Hallgrimskirkja church, explore the museums, and soak in the famous Blue Lagoon.
Relax and float in the famous Dead Sea, known for its high salt content and therapeutic properties. Enjoy mud mask treatments, soak up the unique surroundings, and take in the stunning views.
Visit the vibrant city of Tel Aviv, known for its stunning beaches, lively nightlife, and modern architecture. Explore the historic neighborhood of Jaffa and enjoy delicious Israeli cuisine.

Experience the rich history and religious significance of Jerusalem. Visit iconic sites such as the Western Wall, the Church of the Holy Sepulchre, and the Dome of the Rock. Explore the narrow alleys of the Old City and learn about the city's diverse cultures.

After Brussels, head towards the charming city of Bruges. Spend the next 3 days wandering through its picturesque streets, lined with medieval buildings and romantic canals. Visit the historic Markt square, take a boat ride along the canals, and indulge in the delectable Belgian chocolates. Bruges is often referred to as the 'Venice of the North' for its enchanting beauty.

Brussels, the capital of Belgium, is known for its beautiful architecture, delicious chocolate, and famous waffles. Spend your first 3 days exploring iconic sites like the Grand Place, Atomium, and the Manneken Pis statue. Don't forget to try some authentic Belgian cuisine and sample local beers.

Ghent is a vibrant city with a rich cultural heritage. Explore the medieval city center, visit the stunning Saint Bavo's Cathedral and the famous Ghent Altarpiece. Don't forget to try some local delicacies like Waterzooi and cuberdons.

Antwerp is a dynamic city known for its fashion, art, and diamond trade. Visit the beautiful Antwerp Cathedral, explore the trendy fashion district, and admire the intricate architecture of the Central Station. Don't miss the chance to try Antwerp's famous fries and beer.

Experience the iconic landmarks such as Big Ben, Buckingham Palace, and the Tower of London. Explore world-class museums like the British Museum and Tate Modern. Enjoy vibrant nightlife in Soho and visit the famous West End for a theater performance.

Visit the historic Edinburgh Castle and Royal Mile. Explore the beautiful Holyrood Park and hike up Arthur's Seat for panoramic views. Enjoy the vibrant atmosphere of the Edinburgh Festival if it's during the time of your visit.
Immerse yourself in academic heritage at the prestigious University of Oxford. Explore the historic colleges and punting on the River Thames.
Discover the ancient Roman Baths and Georgian architecture in the picturesque city of Bath. Take a leisurely stroll along the Bath Abbey and visit the Jane Austen Centre.
Explore the iconic Sydney Opera House and take a harbor cruise. Visit the famous Bondi Beach and enjoy a coastal walk. Discover the historic Rocks area and climb the Sydney Harbour Bridge.

Discover the Great Barrier Reef with snorkeling or scuba diving. Explore the Daintree Rainforest and take a scenic railway or cable car ride in Kuranda. Relax on the beautiful beaches and enjoy the tropical climate.

Experience Melbourne's vibrant arts and culture scene. Explore the charming laneways and enjoy the city's world-class coffee and food. Visit the Royal Botanic Gardens and take a scenic drive along the Great Ocean Road.

Brisbane offers a mix of modern attractions and outdoor adventures. Enjoy the city's vibrant riverside dining scene, visit the Queensland Museum and Gallery of Modern Art, and take a day trip to the stunning Moreton Island for sandboarding and dolphin feeding.

Explore the capital city of Western Australia, Perth. Enjoy beautiful city parks like Kings Park and Botanic Garden, visit the Fremantle Prison, take a day trip to Rottnest Island to meet friendly quokkas, and indulge in delicious food and wine in the Swan Valley region.

Visit Ayers Rock, a sacred Aboriginal site and an iconic natural wonder. Witness the breathtaking sunrise and sunset over Uluru, explore the Kata Tjuta rock formations, learn about Aboriginal culture and their connection to the land, and take part in guided walks to discover the unique flora and fauna.
Visit the beautiful Bahá'í Gardens and stroll along the picturesque Carmel Beach.
Discover the charming colonial city of Sucre, known for its well-preserved architecture and historical significance. Visit the Casa de la Libertad and enjoy the local cuisine.
Explore the vibrant capital city of Bolivia known for its stunning views and rich culture. Visit attractions like Plaza Murillo, Witches' Market, and Valle de la Luna.
Embark on an incredible journey to the famous Uyuni Salt Flats, the largest salt flat in the world. Marvel at the expansive white landscape and unique formations.

After your time in La Paz, head south to Uyuni to explore one of the world's largest salt flats, Salar de Uyuni. Spend a day marveling at the endless expanse of white salt, taking perspective-bending photos, and visiting the Isla Incahuasi, an island in the middle of the salt flat. Make sure to catch a sunrise or sunset for an incredible display of colors across the landscape.
Explore the historic Casco Viejo, visit the Panama Canal, and experience the modern skyline of Panama City.
Relax on beautiful beaches, go snorkeling or diving in the crystal-clear waters, and explore the lush rainforests.
Experience the cool mountain climate, hike through scenic trails, and visit coffee plantations.

Buenos Aires is the capital and largest city of Argentina. It is known for its vibrant culture, tango music, and European-style architecture. Spend your days exploring neighborhoods like La Boca and San Telmo, visiting iconic landmarks like the Obelisco and Casa Rosada, and enjoying delicious Argentine cuisine.

Mendoza is located at the foothills of the Andes Mountains and is famous for its vineyards and wineries. Spend your days wine tasting and exploring the beautiful countryside. You can also go hiking or horseback riding in the nearby mountains.

Bariloche is a charming town located in the Patagonian region of Argentina. It is known for its stunning landscapes, including the beautiful Nahuel Huapi Lake and the surrounding mountains. Spend your days hiking, skiing (depending on the season), and enjoying outdoor activities. Don't miss trying the delicious chocolate for which Bariloche is famous.
Discover the famous cloud forests and enjoy adventurous activities like ziplining.
Visit Arenal Volcano National Park and enjoy the natural hot springs.
Relax on beautiful beaches and hike in Manuel Antonio National Park.
Explore the cultural and historical attractions of the capital city.

Oaxaca is known for its rich indigenous culture and colonial architecture. Spend time exploring the charming city, visit Hierve el Agua's petrified waterfalls, and taste the delicious Oaxacan cuisine.

Cancun is famous for its white sandy beaches, turquoise waters, and vibrant nightlife. Enjoy the beachfront resorts, explore the underwater beauty of the Mesoamerican Reef, and take a day trip to the nearby Isla Mujeres.

Mexico City is the capital of Mexico and offers a blend of modern and ancient attractions. Visit the historic center, explore the ancient ruins of Teotihuacan, and indulge in the vibrant food and art scene.

Merida, the capital of Yucatan, is a lively city with a great mix of Mayan and colonial heritage. Explore the architectural wonders, visit the nearby ancient Mayan ruins of Uxmal, and experience the unique Yucatecan culture.
Relax on the beautiful beaches of Playa del Carmen, go snorkeling or diving in the nearby cenotes, and take a day trip to the stunning Mayan ruins of Tulum overlooking the Caribbean Sea.
Relax on pristine white-sand beaches, visit the ancient Mayan city of Tulum, and snorkel in the stunning cenotes of the Riviera Maya.
Experience the vibrant culture, explore the stunning architecture of Hospicio Cabañas, and taste delicious tequila in its birthplace.
Discover the charming colonial city, explore Mayan ruins in nearby Uxmal, and sample Yucatecan specialties like cochinita pibil.
Enjoy the beautiful beaches and vibrant nightlife. Take a boat tour to the Marietas Islands or go snorkeling in the Banderas Bay. Explore the charming Old Town and its cobblestone streets.
Take a flight to Easter Island (Rapa Nui) and explore the mysterious moai statues. Visit archaeological sites like Rano Raraku, Anakena Beach, and enjoy the unique Polynesian culture.
Fly to San Pedro de Atacama, located in the Atacama Desert. Witness surreal landscapes such as the Moon Valley, geysers, salt flats, and enjoy stargazing in one of the world's clearest skies.
Experience the colorful and bohemian coastal city of Valparaíso, visit the UNESCO World Heritage-listed historic quarter, ride the funiculars, and enjoy the street art.
Explore the vibrant capital city of Chile, visit the historic center, La Moneda Palace, Santiago Metropolitan Park, and enjoy the local cuisine.
Head south to Pucon, a picturesque town known for its stunning landscapes. Explore the Villarrica Volcano, visit the hot springs, and enjoy outdoor activities like hiking and kayaking.

Venture into Torres del Paine National Park, famous for its breathtaking landscapes and diverse wildlife. Enjoy hiking among the iconic granite peaks, visit the Grey Glacier, and spot guanacos and condors.
Continue your journey to Puerto Varas, located in the beautiful Lake District region. Admire the stunning views of the Osorno Volcano, explore the German architecture, and indulge in local seafood.
Embark on an Amazon River adventure, spot wildlife and experience indigenous culture
Experience the ancient Inca heritage, visit Machu Picchu and explore the Sacred Valley
Explore the capital city of Peru, visit the historic center and Miraflores district
Explore the stunning Lake Titicaca, visit the floating islands of Uros
Discover the colonial architecture, visit Colca Canyon and observe condors
Discover the rich history at the Royal Palace and Silver Pagoda, learn about the Khmer Rouge regime at Tuol Sleng Genocide Museum, and take a boat trip to explore the Mekong River.
Enjoy the scenic riverside town, visit the Bokor National Park and climb the Bokor Hill Station, take a river cruise to see fireflies, and try the famous Kampot pepper.
Relax on the stunning beaches, go snorkeling or scuba diving in the crystal-clear waters, and explore the nearby islands like Koh Rong and Koh Ta Kiev.
Explore the magnificent temples of Angkor Wat and Angkor Thom. Visit the floating village of Kompong Phluk and enjoy a traditional Apsara dance performance.

Explore the vibrant capital city of Cuba known for its rich history, colorful architecture, and lively atmosphere. Visit iconic landmarks such as El Capitolio, Plaza de la Catedral, and the Malecon. Enjoy the music and dance scene in the lively streets of Old Havana.

Relax and unwind at the beautiful beaches of Varadero. Enjoy the crystal-clear waters, white sandy beaches, and luxurious resorts. Take part in water activities such as snorkeling, diving, or sailing. Indulge in delicious seafood and tropical cocktails.

Travel to the UNESCO World Heritage Site of Trinidad, famous for its well-preserved Spanish colonial architecture. Enjoy the cobblestone streets, pastel-colored colonial buildings, and visit the nearby beautiful Playa Ancon beach for some relaxation.
Escape to the cool hill country. Visit tea plantations, enjoy the picturesque scenery, and take a scenic train ride. Explore Horton Plains National Park and hike to World's End.
Experience the colonial charm of Galle Fort. Walk along the fort walls, visit the lighthouse, and explore the narrow streets filled with Dutch-inspired architecture. Relax at Unawatuna Beach.
Discover the cultural heart of Sri Lanka. Visit the Temple of the Tooth, Peradeniya Botanical Gardens, and enjoy a traditional dance performance. Take a day trip to Sigiriya or Dambulla.
Explore the capital city with its mix of modern and colonial architecture. Visit the National Museum, Gangaramaya Temple, and Galle Face Green. Enjoy shopping and dining in the city center.
Marvel at the stunning views from Ella Rock, visit the Nine Arch Bridge, and hike to Little Adam's Peak.
Visit the world-famous Taj Mahal, a UNESCO World Heritage site and one of the Seven Wonders of the World. Explore the Agra Fort and immerse yourself in the Mughal architecture and history.
Experience the rich history and culture of India's capital city. Visit iconic landmarks such as the Red Fort and Jama Masjid, explore the narrow lanes of Old Delhi, and enjoy delicious street food.

Experience the spiritual city of Varanasi on the banks of the Ganges River. Witness the mesmerizing Ganga Aarti ceremony, take a boat ride along the ghats, and explore the ancient temples and narrow alleys.

Discover the vibrant city of Jaipur, often called the Pink City. Explore magnificent palaces like the Hawa Mahal and Amer Fort, shop for local handicrafts at the bazaars, and indulge in traditional Rajasthani cuisine.

Discover the bustling city of Mumbai, visit the iconic Gateway of India and explore the historical sites of Elephanta Caves. Stroll along the Marine Drive promenade, visit the vibrant markets, and try the famous street food. Experience the vibrant nightlife and Bollywood culture.
Explore ancient temples, interact with elephants, and immerse yourself in traditional Thai culture
Relax on stunning beaches, indulge in water activities, and explore the nearby islands
Return to Bangkok for shopping, street food and final exploration before departure
Discover the breathtaking limestone cliffs, go rock climbing, and take a boat tour to Phi Phi Islands
Experience pristine beaches, visit waterfalls, go snorkeling or diving, and enjoy the lively nightlife.
Explore ancient ruins, historical temples, and learn about the rich history of the former capital of Thailand.

fields.name: Panthéon
fields.description: The Panthéon is a monument in the 5th arrondissement of Paris, France. It stands in the Latin Quarter, atop the Montagne Sainte-Geneviève, in the centre of the Place du Panthéon, which was named after it. The edifice was built between 1758 and 1790, from designs by Jacques-Germain Soufflot, at the behest of King Louis XV of France; the king intended it as a church dedicated to Saint Genevieve, Paris's patron saint, whose relics were to be housed in the church. Neither Soufflot nor Louis XV lived to see the church completed.

Before that, seismologists believed Earth's core to be a single molten sphere, being unable, however, to explain careful measurements of seismic waves from earthquakes, which were inconsistent with this idea. Lehmann analysed the seismic wave measurements and concluded that Earth must have a solid inner core and a molten outer core to produce seismic waves that matched the measurements. fields.name: Melbourne Mint
fields.description: The Melbourne Mint, in Melbourne, Australia, was a branch of the British Royal Mint. It minted gold sovereigns from 1872 until 1931, and half-sovereigns (intermittently) from 1873 until 1915. In 1916 it commenced minting Commonwealth silver threepences, sixpences, shillings and florins. From 1923 it minted all pre-decimal denominations. It minted rarities such as the 1921/22 overdate threepence, 1923 half-penny and 1930 penny, as well as Australia's four commemorative florins in 1927 (Canberra), 1934/35, 1951 and 1954. It assisted the Royal Australian Mint in Canberra in producing one cent coins from 1966 to 1968 and two cent coins in 1966. From 1969 all coin production moved to the Royal Australian Mint in Canberra, and the building housing the coin minting equipment was demolished shortly afterwards. The remaining administrative building is now the home of the Royal Historical Society of Victoria, and has been leased to the private sector since 2001.

It was first constructed starting in 1839, and during its operation as a prison between 1845 and 1924, it held and executed some of Australia's most notorious criminals, including bushranger Ned Kelly and serial killer Frederick Bailey Deeming. In total, 133 people were executed by hanging. Though it was used briefly during World War II, it formally ceased operating as a prison in 1924; with parts of the jail being incorporated into the RMIT University, and the rest becoming a museum.

fields.name: Haifa City Museum
fields.description:
The Haifa City Museum was inaugurated in November 2000 as the historical City Museum.
Its location, at the edge of Haifa's German Colony and near the historical part of the city, affords a view of a rich and complex urban fabric that reveals the historical diversity of the city's different populations. As part of the museum's cultural activities, it mounts exhibitions on themes related to the city's physical and spiritual core. Historically, Haifa has been a hub of different cultures and a meeting point between East and West. Set at its heart and attentive to its different aspects, the museum opens a space for socio-political debates that emerge in the urban environment.

The port employs over 1,000 people, rising to 5,000 when cruise ships dock in Haifa. The Port of Haifa lies to the north of Haifa's downtown quarter on the Mediterranean, and stretches to some three kilometres along the city's central shore with activities ranging from military, industrial and commercial next to a nowadays-smaller passenger cruising facility.

fields.description: The Siem Reap River is a river flowing through Siem Reap Province, in north-west Cambodia. The Siem Reap River was originally an offtake channel constructed during the Angkor period, used to divert water from the Puok River southward, probably to the East Baray. Because of the straight nature of a channel, the water flowed much faster than in a natural river. This caused the bed of the channel to erode as much as 10 meters in some areas, and probably caused problems with diverting the water to the East Baray. Over the past thousand years, the channel has gained small meanders and a unique ecosystem, and thus it is more accurate to call it a river.

fields.name: Agra Fort
fields.description: The Agra Fort is a historical fort in the city of Agra, and also known as Agra's Red Fort. Mughal emperor Humayun was crowned at this fort. It was later renovated by the Mughal emperor Akbar from 1565 and the present-day structure was completed in 1573. It served as the main residence of the rulers of the Mughal dynasty until 1638, when the capital was shifted from Agra to Delhi. It was also known as the "Lal-Qila" or "Qila-i-Akbari". Before capture by the British, the last Indian rulers to have occupied it were the Marathas. In 1983, the Agra fort was inscribed as a UNESCO World Heritage Site because of its importance during the Mughal Dynasty. It is about 2.5 kilometers (1.6 mi) northwest of its more famous sister monument, the Taj Mahal. The fort can be more accurately described as a walled city. It was later renovated by Shah Jahan.

fields.description: The India Gate is a war memorial located near the Kartavya path on the eastern edge of the "ceremonial axis" of New Delhi, formerly called Rajpath. It stands as a memorial to 84,000 soldiers of the British Indian Army who died between 1914 and 1921 in the First World War, in France, Flanders, Mesopotamia, Persia, East Africa, Gallipoli and elsewhere in the Near and the Far East, and the Third Anglo-Afghan War. 13,300 servicemen's names, including some soldiers and officers from the United Kingdom, are inscribed on the gate. Designed by Sir Edwin Lutyens, the gate evokes the architectural style of the memorial arch such as the Arch of Constantine, in Rome, and is often compared to the Arc de Triomphe in Paris, and the Gateway of India in Mumbai.
